http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm75.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Signature stuff </span><hr size=1> To get a signature banner, the best place to go is FlamingText.com<br>
<br>
Its free and easy to use.  One you get it, you then have to put it somewhere on the web that you can link to.  Many places give free webpage space and since your only going to need a few K of space, any should do fine.<br>
<br>
One its on the web, you need to tell EZBoard where to find it.  Go to My Control Panel and then into Edit Preferences.  You'll find the Signature area there.<br>
<br>
In the Signature area, add in something that looks like this<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre>  &lt;center&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://YOURWEBPAGE/YOURLOGO&quot; 
border=0&gt;&lt;/center&gt;</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
Replace YOURWEBPAGE with the Web Site and YOURLOGO with the name of your banner.<br>
<br>
Thats about it.  With a little work with HTML, you can start to do other things like make it link to your email address or other cool stuff.  Just search GOOGLE for HTML How-To's.<br>
<br>
